</ul>
</p>
<p>The command line is a treasure trove of automation and productivity enhancements. Not to mention it is seemingly a lost art. It seems as though, more and more, when I tell people to fire up a command line and run a specific command I am greeted with a groan. Is the command line truly dying? Or do I just hang out with too many GUIites?
</p>